Overview
========

nss-tls is a name resolving library for glibc
(https://www.gnu.org/software/libc/), which performs DNS queries over HTTPS
through 1.1.1.1 (https://developers.cloudflare.com/1.1.1.1/dns-over-https/).

Usage
=====

Assuming your system runs glibc (https://www.gnu.org/software/libc/) and systemd
(https://www.freedesktop.org/wiki/Software/systemd/):

  1) meson --prefix=/usr build
  2) ninja -C build install
  3) systemctl daemon-reload
  4) systemctl start nss-tlsd
  5) Add "tls" to the "hosts" entry in /etc/nsswitch.conf

